name: future
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.18.2" %}


package:
  name: future
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/f/future/future-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b1bead90b70cf6ec3f0710ae53a525360fa360d306a86583adc6bf83a4db537d

build:
  number: 5
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"
  entry_points:
    - futurize = libfuturize.main:main
    - pasteurize = libpasteurize.main:main

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  commands:
    - futurize -h
    - pasteurize -h

  imports:
    - future

about:
  home: http://python-future.org
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Clean single-source support for Python 3 and 2
  description: |
    Python-future  is the missing compatibility layer between Python 2 and
    Python 3. It allows you to use a single, clean Python 3.x-compatible
    codebase to support both Python 2 and Python 3 with minimal overhead.
  doc_url: http://python-future.org
  dev_url: https://github.com/PythonCharmers/python-future

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jakirkham
    - mmysinger
    - ocefpaf
